✅ Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates the implementation of an Adaptive Noise-Robust Offline Voice-Controlled Embedded System using TinyML on ESP32 hardware.

The integration of:

Adaptive Noise Filtering

MFCC Feature Extraction

TinyML Keyword Spotting

Embedded Edge Inference

enables efficient, real-time, and privacy-preserving voice interaction on low-power embedded devices.

The project validates the practicality of deploying intelligent voice interfaces directly on edge hardware without cloud dependency, highlighting the growing potential of TinyML in modern embedded and IoT applications.


